In this article, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. recognizes and honors the contributions of Native peoples during National Native American Heritage Month. He acknowledges the historical oppression and violence faced by Native communities and emphasizes their resilience and pride. The President highlights his efforts to champion a new chapter in the Nation-to-Nation relationships, including appointing Native Americans to key positions in his administration and making historic investments in Indian Country. He also discusses initiatives to address the impacts of harmful federal policies, improve public health and safety, and protect sacred lands and waters. President Biden urges all Americans to observe National Native American Heritage Month and celebrate Native American Heritage Day on November 24, 2023.